    DateInput

    StableAccessible

    Date input allows the user to easily input a specific date or a date range. By default, HDS date input is supplied with a date picker functionality.

    • Usage
    • Code
    • Accessibility

    Code

    Code examples

    Date input with a picker

    • React
    Press Enter to start editing. Press Esc to stop editing.
    import { DateInput } from 'hds-react';
    

    () => (
      <div style={{maxWidth: '400px'}}>
        <DateInput
          helperText="Use format D.M.YYYY"
          id="date-input-example-1"
          initialMonth={new Date()}
          label="Choose a date"
          language="en"
          onChange={function noRefCheck(){}}
          required
        />
      </div>
    )

    Date input without a confirmation

    Press Enter to start editing. Press Esc to stop editing.

    )

    Localised date inputs

    • React
    Press Enter to start editing. Press Esc to stop editing.

    () => (
      <div style={{maxWidth: '400px'}}>
        <DateInput
          helperText="Use format D.M.YYYY"

          label="Choose a date"
          language="en"
          onChange={function noRefCheck(){}}
          required
          style={{marginBottom: 'var(--spacing-s)'}}
        />
    

        <DateInput
          helperText="Kyt muotoa P.K.VVVV"
          id="date-input-example-5"
          initialMonth={new Date()}

          language="fi"

          required
          style={{marginBottom: 'var(--spacing-s)'}}

          required

    )

    Properties

    Note! You can find the full list of properties in the React Storybook.

    Also, note that this component is an input. All features supported by the HDS TextInput are also supported by this component. See TextInput documentation page for more information.

    PropertyDescriptionValuesDefault value
    helperTextHelper text to be displayed below the input.string-
    errorTextError text to be displayed below the input.string-
    successTextSuccess text to be displayed below the input.string-
    infoTextInfo text to be displayed below the input.string-
    initialMonthThe initial month open in calendar.Date-
    labelA text label for the input.string-
    onChangeCallback fired when the state is changed.event-
    languageLanguage of the date input.string (fi, en, sv)en
    minDateMinimum date to show in the datepicker calendar.DateStart of the month ten years before current date
    maxDateMaximum date to show in the datepicker calendar.DateEnd of the month ten years from current date.
    isDateDisabledByDisables date(s) based on conditional function.function-
    initialMonthThe initial month open in calendar.Date-
    disableDatePickerIf set to true, the date picker button is hidden.booleanfalse
    disableConfirmationIf set to true, the date picker does not require confirmation.booleanfalse
